Using the definition of binomial coefficients, $\dbinom{n}{k} = \frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}$, we calculate $\dbinom{31}{28}$ as follows:
$$
\begin{aligned}
\dbinom{31}{28} &= \dfrac{31!}{28!(31-28)!}\\
&\approx 4.74 \times 10^{20}
\end{aligned}
$$
Therefore, $\boxed{\dbinom{31}{28} \approx 4.74 \times 10^{20}}$. The answer is: 4740000000000000000000.
